        <body><div type="bibliography">
                
                <p><bibl><ptr target="#boardman-hayes1966"/>, p. 169, n. <citedRange>425</citedRange> (ph., dr.)</bibl>; 
                    <bibl><ptr target="#cdl1970"/>, p. 252, <citedRange>k)</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>001910</citedRange></bibl>.
                Cf. <bibl><ptr target="#cdl2015a"/>, p. <citedRange>67</citedRange></bibl>.</p>             
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> <supplied reason="lost">τᾶ</supplied>ι 
                    <persName type="divine" ref="#Kore"><name nymRef="Κόρα">Κόραι</name></persName> 
                    τὰ<unclear>ν</unclear> <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>
	 </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p/>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="fr" xml:space="preserve">
            <p><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> pour Korè la <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="en" xml:space="preserve">
            <p><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> for Kore the <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="en" xml:space="preserve">
            <p><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> per Kore la <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>.</p>
            </div><div type="commentary">
                
                <p><bibl><ptr target="#cdl1970"/></bibl> was sceptical about the attribution of the graffito to Cyrenaica, but later finds, probably known at the time by the editors 
                    and later published in <bibl><ptr target="#boardman-hayes1973"/></bibl> (whence <ref type="inscription" source="#IGCyr2">IGCyr003800</ref> and <ref type="inscription" source="#IGCyr2">IGCyr003900</ref>) 
                    now lead to accept it as inscribed on the spot.</p> 
            </div></body>
